13/11/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Serbia-Montenegro President Svetozar Marovic arrived for his first official visit to Sarajevo on Thursday (13 November). 
His delegation will participate in the interstate co-operation council after meeting the three members of the BiH presidency. 
The meeting of the council is expected to tackle border and economic issues, as well as problems with the rights and status of BiH citizens living in Serbia-Montenegro.
In other news, BiH Foreign Minister Mladen Ivanic told local reporters Wednesday that the country's membership in NATO is inevitable. 
He added that BiH would join the Alliance with a small army of 3,000 to 5,000 professional soldiers. 
(FENA, BBC - 13/11/03; SRNA, FENA, BBC - 12/11/03)
